Nice brain stimulating game.  Moderately easy for a "brainiac" like myself.   Evo walks along isometric structures to the finish line of each level.  You manipulate the structure to move walls, channels, or the entire structure.  In certain places have to move Evo over buttons to open new areas to explore.    These structures don't follow logical constructs of the real world.  Two platforms can line up in such a way that can visually be connected, even though in reality they would be disconnected.  Also, if a pathway has a gap and cannot be crossed, putting a column visually in front of the gap now allows Evo to cross.  Once you figure out the mechanics of the world, the game becomes an interesting challenge.

content: Monuments style puzzle game (but harder)

You guys did a good job on this game to begin this I would like to say that the puzzles were really good, I was stumped a few times which made it fun instead of frustrating when you can't figure it out at all. The music was really nice and soothing and at certain points of the game, the music went a little darker which gave it a mysterious vibe. I will recommend anyone to put on a good pair of headphones if you're going to play this game. The graphics were great though I must say that I feel it was lacking a scenery unlike in Monument Valley, where you see clouds, towers, trees, structures, ruins etc. The real problem for me though was the story of this game but for the sake of keeping this review spoiler free, I will let everyone play the game for themselves and let them build their own opinion on that. Overall this is not a bad game at all and I definitely recommend this game to anyone who has played Monument Valley or any other puzzle game in general.

replyContent:
Unfortunately, this is a common problem for Google Play and it has nothing to do with the game itself.
People advice to go to Settings -- Apps -- All Select Play Store: Clear Cache & Data & Uninstall updates.
GP will restore updates automatically and this should fix the issue.

content: If you love Monument Valley you'll love this too

Anyone that has played monument valley will feel at home with this. Visually and puzzle-wise it's similar but different. Puzzles are a bit more complex; there are more 2D/3D mind-bending mechanics (a la Escher); and the story is a bit more developed & less gnomic. And like MV it's fun, but fairly brief.

I never played Monument Valley so I'm coming into this review without any bias (not sure if that is good or bad).  Also, I have not yet completed every level.  This puzzle game is really well done.  The graphics are really nice, the music is soothing, the short cut-scenes are entertaining and I have not experienced any problems at all. Most importantly, the game is incredibly fun!  You have to make sure to take a "step back" and enjoy the puzzles/illusions in their entirety instead of just focusing on solving the level.  I would definitely recommend this to anyone looking for this style of game.
